The North West Legislature Public Accounts Committee (Scopa) will on Wednesday hold an oversight meeting with Social Development MEC Hoffman Galeng and management to discuss reports that taxpayers are paying security guards at his private home in Vryburg.
According to weekend media reports, the North West social development department is spending R50,000 a month to pay four guards working two per shift at the MEC’s home in Vryburg while he stays at his official home in Mahikeng.
The oversight meeting will be held at the legislature at 3pm on Wednesday.
